# Task: Add Git-Based Version Control for Auto-Evolving Malloy Models

## Context
The conversational analytics system can now propose model changes when queries fail due to missing fields. The Malloy source files are already in a git repo. We'll use git to track all auto-generated changes, giving us full history, easy rollback, and visibility into how the model evolves.

## Malloy Source Files Location
`~/repos/Malloy Test/Malloy-source-files/` (already a git repo)

## Your Task

### Step 1: Verify Git State
```bash
cd ~/repos/Malloy\ Test/Malloy-source-files
git status
git log --oneline -5
```

Confirm current state and note the HEAD commit as our baseline.

### Step 2: Update Model Enhancement Logic

Modify `model-enhancer.js` to commit after every change:
```javascript
async function applyModelChange(change) {
  const { file, code, reasoning, userQuestion } = change;
  
  // 1. Read current file
  // 2. Insert new code in appropriate section
  // 3. Write file
  
  // 4. Git commit with descriptive message
  await exec(`git add ${file}`);
  await exec(`git commit -m "Auto: Add ${change.changeType} for: ${userQuestion}" -m "Reasoning: ${reasoning}" -m "Code added:\n${code}"`);
  
  // 5. Return commit hash for reference
  const hash = await exec('git rev-parse --short HEAD');
  return { success: true, commitHash: hash };
}
```

### Step 3: Add Rollback Capability
```javascript
async function rollbackLastChange() {
  await exec('git revert HEAD --no-edit');
  // Trigger Publisher reload
  return { success: true, message: 'Reverted last model change' };
}

async function rollbackToCommit(hash) {
  await exec(`git revert ${hash}..HEAD --no-edit`);
  return { success: true };
}
```

